    <section class="info">
        <h1>Rules</h1>
        <p>There will be a central section will have a circle in it. Data packets will emerge at the outside and move towards the centre. Your role is to highlight each data packet and then classify the level of danger it represents.</p>
        <p>When you select the data packet another section will be populated with a selection of information each of which can provide either positive, neutral or negative responses. If there are 0 negative attributes then please classify the data packet as friendly, if there are 1-2 then as suspect and 3-4 as hostile.</p>
        <h2>Attributes</h2>
        <p>Checksum Value: Valid/Invalid/Zero all are neutral</p>
        <p>Time of receiving data packet: 24 hour clock all are neutral</p>
        <p>IP Address: random IP address all are neutral</p>
        <p>Country: chosen from the made up list all are neutral</p>
        <p>Port Number: 4444 = hostile, 80 = safe</p>
        <p>Protocol: ICMP = hostile, HTTPS = safe</p>
        <p>Fragmentation: Yes= hostile, No = safe</p>
        <p>Certificates: Expired = hostile, Valid = safe</p>
        <button>Start Trial</button>
    </section>

